Male : Similar to female except for sexual characters. Antenna slightly more verticillate than female, with 14 flagellomeres. Proboscis length 1.29–1.30 mm, about 0.99 of forefemur length. Maxillary palpus dark, length 0.11 mm. Wing length 1.88–1.94 mm. Genitalia (
Fig. 2
): tergum VIII covered with broad scales intermixed with minute setae on distal half, long setae on distal margin; sternum VIII covered with broad scales and minute setae on the distal half, long setae in one row on the distal margin. Tergum IX with large interlobar space, 2 dorsolateral lobes, each lobe with 2 foliform setae expanded apically, strongly sclerotized.
